WINE
Graham's 'Malvedos' Vintage Port 1984
Founded in 1820, W. & J. Graham & Co.
maintains its place as one of the most prestigious names in
fine Port wines — many experts agreeing that Graham is the
single finest Port wine vintner. Young Vintage Ports are fortified
with brandy and vinified naturally, without benefit of clarification
or filtration — generally taking at least a decade to mature during
which a sediment precipitates in each bottle. Careful decanting
results in a brilliantly clear, sweet, ruby-red dessert wine of
unequaled charm. Graham's 1984 Vintage Port fulfills its
rich heritage with bold brambleberry and plum flavors
slowly mellowed to a satin texture.
